PHOENIX GROUP Inc. said its board approved a 2-for-1 stock split, payable to shares of record Oct. 16.
The split will be payable within 30 days of the record date.
The Irvine, Calif., investment company currently has about 2.6 million common shares outstanding.
Phoenix Group also said it expects to post a record gain in net assets for the third quarter of more than $20 million, or more than $1.70 a share on a fully diluted basis.
That compares with an increase of more than $3.8 million, or about 30 cents a share, in the second quarter. 

